-- Spanish inflation to return below two percent: minister
-- 
-- Mon Oct 1, 2012 8:38am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/10/01/us-spain-economy-inflation-idUSBRE8900KW20121001

 

 MADRID  (Reuters) - Spanish inflation will return to below 2 percent once the one-off effect from a hike in Value Added Tax fades, Economy Minister Luis de Guindos said at a news conference on Monday. 
 Official data show inflation was 3.5 percent in September. (Reporting By Sarah Morris; Writing by Tracy Rucinski; Editing by Nigel Davies)